TITLE:"AB-900: Microsoft 365 Copilot and Agent Administration Fundamentals"
ID:01|TYPE:"SINGLE"|QUESTION:"Which component of the Copilot System provides the context of user data, such as emails, calendars, and chats?"|OPTIONS:"The Large Language Model (LLM)","Microsoft Graph","Azure Active Directory","Windows 11 Kernel"|ANSWER:"B"|EXPLANATION:"Microsoft Graph is the gateway to data and intelligence in Microsoft 365; it provides the grounding data for Copilot."|POINTS:1
ID:02|TYPE:"MULTI"|QUESTION:"What are 2 technical requirements for a user to access Microsoft 365 Copilot? (Choose 2)"|OPTIONS:"A Microsoft 365 E3 or E5 license","A dedicated NVIDIA GPU in the local machine","Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise installed","An active Azure Subscription for every end-user"|ANSWER:"A","C"|EXPLANATION:"Users need a qualifying base license (like E3/E5) and the Enterprise version of the productivity apps."|POINTS:1
ID:03|TYPE:"FILL"|QUESTION:"To prevent users from over-sharing sensitive information through Copilot, administrators should implement the principle of {{BLANK}}."|OPTIONS:"Global Administration","Conditional Access","Least Privilege","Multi-factor Authentication"|ANSWER:"C"|EXPLANATION:"The principle of Least Privilege (or 'Just Enough Access') ensures Copilot only accesses data the user is already authorized to see."|POINTS:1
ID:04|TYPE:"YESNO"|QUESTION:"Regarding data privacy and security in Microsoft 365 Copilot:"|STATEMENTS:"Copilot uses your tenant data to train the global LLM","Copilot inherits the existing permissions of the logged-in user","Copilot can access password-protected files if the user owns them"|ANSWER:"No","Sí","No"|EXPLANATION:"Microsoft does not use tenant data to train the foundation models, and it respects standard permissioning."|POINTS:1
ID:05|TYPE:"DRAG"|QUESTION:"Order the steps to prepare a tenant for Copilot deployment:"|ITEMS:"Verify technical prerequisites and licensing","Review data permissions and SharePoint access","Assign Copilot licenses to pilot users","Establish a 'Center of Excellence' for adoption"|EXPLANATION:"Technical prep → Data governance → Licensing → Organizational adoption."|POINTS:1
ID:06|TYPE:"MATCH"|QUESTION:"Match the tool to its primary function in the Copilot ecosystem:"|STATEMENTS:"Copilot Studio","Microsoft 365 Admin Center","Viva Insights","Purview"|OPTIONS:"Creating custom agents and plugins","Managing license assignments","Measuring adoption and usage patterns","Data classification and labeling"|ANSWER:"A","B","C","D"|EXPLANATION:"Studio is for building, Admin Center for management, Viva for metrics, and Purview for security."|POINTS:1ID:01|TYPE:"DRAG"|QUESTION:"Ordena las fases de despliegue de Copilot:"|ITEMS:"Identificar casos de uso piloto","Configurar permisos y governance","Habilitar licencias","Medir adopción y ROI"|EXPLANATION:"Casos de uso → governance → licencias → medición."|POINTS:1
ID:07|TYPE:"MATCH"|QUESTION:"Empareja cada herramienta con su uso principal:"|STATEMENTS:"Power BI","Power Apps","Power Automate"|OPTIONS:"Análisis de datos","Creación de apps","Flujos de trabajo"|ANSWER:"A","B","C"|EXPLANATION:"BI=Análisis, Apps=Apps, Automate=Flujos."|POINTS:1
